    <h1>THE LORD OF THE RINGS</h1>
    <p>
        “The Lord of the Rings” is an epic fantasy story written by J.R.R. Tolkien.
It takes place in a world called Middle-earth, a place filled with ancient kingdoms, magical beings, and long-forgotten histories. 
        </p>
<p>
        The story is set thousands of years after a great war in which the Dark Lord Sauron created the One Ring, a powerful object meant to control the wills of others and bring all life under his rule.

    </p>
<p>
        For many years the Ring was lost, until it was found by a hobbit named Bilbo Baggins.
        </p>
<p>
        Hobbits are small, peaceful people who live quietly in a land called the Shire, far from the troubles of the outside world.
        Later the Ring passes to Bilbo’s nephew, Frodo, who learns that Sauron has returned and is searching for it. 
    </p>
<p>
        If Sauron gets the Ring back, every kingdom and civilization in Middle-earth will fall.

    </p>
<p>
        Realizing the danger, the wizard Gandalf helps form a group called the Fellowship of the Ring. 
        </p>
<p>
        This group includes Frodo and his hobbit friends Sam, Merry, and Pippin; the human warriors Aragorn and Boromir; the elf prince Legolas; and the dwarf Gimli.
        </p>
<p>
        Together they set out on a long and dangerous journey to take the Ring to Mount Doom — the only place where it can be destroyed.

As the journey progresses, the Fellowship faces battles, betrayal, and overwhelming odds.
        </p>
<p>
        The group is eventually separated, and each member follows a different path. Frodo and Sam continue toward Mordor, guided (and sometimes misled) by Gollum, a tormented creature who once possessed the Ring and wants it back.
        </p>
<p>
        Meanwhile, Aragorn, Legolas, and Gimli help lead the fight against Sauron’s armies, forming alliances with the people of Rohan and Gondor. 
    </p>
<p>
        Great battles such as Helm’s Deep and the Pelennor Fields decide the fate of entire nations.

What makes The Lord of the Rings special is not only the battles or the magic, but the deeper themes behind them. 
        </p>
<p>
        The story is about friendship, loyalty, and the strength to do what is right even when the world feels hopeless.
        </p>
<p>
        It shows how ordinary people — like hobbits — can change history simply by being kind, brave, and determined. It also explores the danger of power, the temptation of evil, and the importance of hope even in the darkest moments.

    </p>
<p>
        The story is told in three books — The Fellowship of the Ring, The Two Towers, and The Return of the King — and has become one of the most influential and beloved works in modern literature.
    </p>
<p>
        It has inspired millions of readers and viewers through books, movies, games, and art, and it remains a cornerstone of fantasy storytelling.
    </p>
